                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 167/81.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill states that the Chinese Government prefers that the Lienchou
                    settlement be made by an exchange of notes. Mr. Rockhill says that he has seen
                    the draft, which includes everything essential in draft of the agreement which
                    he sent to the department. He advises that the matter be concluded in this
                    way.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
